  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The Hunger Project/Epicenter strategy is a community based development strategy that will
      positively affect health, education, empowerment, and consumption.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The investigators propose a randomized controlled design that will measure how The Hunger
      Projects' intervention affects the lives of Ghanaians. A pre-intervention baseline survey of
      approximately 4,000 households with over 20,000 individuals and two follow-up surveys of the
      same households will be conducted over the ten year experimental period.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
